# Cursor Standards Adapter

Use the repo-level canonical governance files as the primary source of truth:

- Read `AGENTS.md`
- Read `RULES.md`
- Use `rules/`, `skills/`, `.bbg/context/`, and `.bbg/policy/`
- Prefer `bbg analyze`, `bbg start "<task>"`, `bbg resume <task-id>`, and `bbg status`
- When resuming a task, prefer `.bbg/tasks/<task-id>/context.json`, then `handoff.md`, then `decisions.json`
- If the tool was launched by `bbg`, prefer `BBG_TASK_*`, `BBG_LOOP_*`, `BBG_HANDOFF_PATH`, `BBG_CONTEXT_PATH`, `BBG_RESUME_STRATEGY`, and `BBG_RECOVERY_PLAN`
